put a ring around
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:expressing certainty, strong agreement, etc. [? from hoop-la; or from ringing e.g. a calendar or diary date; or marking off something as one's own]
Origin:[none]
Register: informal

Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: esp. in 2nd person you can put a ring around it/that
Citations
Date: 0/0/1998
Source: Passionate Pen, The
Author: McALPINE
Vol / Page: 104
Edition:
Quote: There are so many writers trying to get in [sc. to Mills and Boon publications], but with a number of people you can put a ring around it: they write what they want and it's not what the publishers want.
Notes:

